com.hcl.domino.data

Enum FTIndex

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<FTIndex>
      • com.hcl.domino.data.FTIndex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    INumberEnum<Short>, Serializable, Comparable<FTIndex>

    public enum FTIndex
extends Enum<FTIndex>
implements INumberEnum<Short>
    These values define the options used when creating a full text index for a database.
    These options may be combined as a Set.
    However, AUTOOPTIONS will ignore all other indexing options and therefore should not be OR-ed with any of the other indexing options.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • REINDEX

        public static final FTIndex REINDEX
        Forces re-indexing the database from scratch. This option is useful if the indexing options for the database are being changed.

      • CASE_SENSITIVE

        public static final FTIndex CASE_SENSITIVE
        Build case sensitive index

      • STEM_INDEX

        public static final FTIndex STEM_INDEX
        Build an index that includes word variants (stems). This allows searching to include word variants. A full text search index built with the Notes user interface, is automatically stemmed.

      • INDEX_SENTENCE_PARAGRAPH_BREAKS

        public static final FTIndex INDEX_SENTENCE_PARAGRAPH_BREAKS
        Build index with word, sentence, and paragraph index break option which allows a search for words within a sentence or paragraph.

      • OPTIMIZE

        public static final FTIndex OPTIMIZE
        Optimize index (e.g. for CDROM) (Not used)

      • INDEX_ATTACHED_FILES

      • ENCRYPTED_FIELDS

        public static final FTIndex ENCRYPTED_FIELDS
        Index Encrypted Fields

      • AUTOOPTIONS

        public static final FTIndex AUTOOPTIONS
        Use the index options that are in database. If the database has never been indexed, use the default indexing options. Database indexing options include the Stop Word File name, case sensitivity, the PSW option, reindexing, and the stem index. Note that the stem index will be set if AUTOOPTIONS is used.

      • SUMMARY_ONLY
